{
  "stem": "25639.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Little did I know at the time that there were thousands of camps, concentration camps, a whole network of concentration camps throughout Germany.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What happened to the sonderkommando who did this act?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I first was transferred to another job with my mother and my sister.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was called the [SPEAKING GERMAN] The [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's interesting that nobody seems to know about the [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And many years later, my sister and I talked about the [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It really means weavery, or a place where one weaves, in German, but our job there was to process the clothes that was not fit to be sent to Germany.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "For what we did with the clothes in the Kanada work detail, was we packaged them for shipment to Germany.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Yes, the German folk wore our clothes from home during World War II.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Now, the clothes that were not fit to be worn, apparently, was cut up in-- into strips about this wide and-- somewhere else, not where I worked.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Maybe in another barrack nearby.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And somebody sewed up the ends.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But by the time these strips reached us, they were just piles of-- heaps of-- of these things.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We had to twirl them, and we had to braid them, just like hair.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We braid-- we braided them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And little do I know what they used them for.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I have since done some research, and there were two theories.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And one was that they were used on German submarines during World War II, in order to seal the open areas, areas that can open up.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And also that they were used for fuse on-- out in the front, in the battlefield.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So whether this is correct or not, I'm not certain.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
